[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man, 19, bailed after holidaymaker dies in Gower crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 19-year-old man has been released on police bail following a fatal crash on Gower.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police were called to the Cefn Bryn mountain road near Reynoldston at 22:55 BST on Friday after a Rover and Kia Proceed collided.
The driver of the Rover died and has been named as Timothy Malone, 67, from Eastleigh in Hampshire.
Mr Malone was on holiday in Gower with his wife, who remains in a stable condition at Morriston Hospital.
Two men who were passengers in the the Kia were treated for minor injuries at hospital and have since been discharged.
